Document: Curve
Path: godot/classes/class_curve.rst
Summary: Describes the Curve resource, its purpose, and the concept of unit curves.

This resource describes a mathematical curve by defining a set of points and tangents at each point. By default, it ranges between 0 and 1 on the X and Y axes, but these ranges can be changed.

Note: Many resources and nodes assume they are given unit curves. A unit curve is a curve whose domain (the X axis) is between 0 and 1. Some examples of unit curve usage are CPUParticles2D.angle_curve and Line2D.width_curve.
---CHUNK---
