Path: godot/classes/class_curve.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties of the Curve class, including bake resolution, domain and value limits, point count, and individual point properties like mode, tangent, and position.

Properties:
bake_resolution (int): The number of points to include in the baked (i.e. cached) curve data. Default: 100.
Method: set_bake_resolution(value: int)
Method: get_bake_resolution()

max_domain (float): The maximum domain (x-coordinate) that points can have. Default: 1.0.
Method: set_max_domain(value: float)
Method: get_max_domain()

max_value (float): The maximum value (y-coordinate) that points can have. Tangents can cause higher values between points. Default: 1.0.
Method: set_max_value(value: float)
Method: get_max_value()

min_domain (float): The minimum domain (x-coordinate) that points can have. Default: 0.0.
Method: set_min_domain(value: float)
Method: get_min_domain()

min_value (float): The minimum value (y-coordinate) that points can have. Tangents can cause lower values between points. Default: 0.0.
Method: set_min_value(value: float)
Method: get_min_value()

point_count (int): The number of points describing the curve. Default: 0.
Method: set_point_count(value: int)
Method: get_point_count()

point_{index}/left_mode (int): The left TangentMode for the point at index. Default: 0. Note: index is a value in the 0 .. point_count - 1 range.

point_{index}/left_tangent (float): The left tangent angle (in degrees) for the point at index. Default: 0.0. Note: index is a value in the 0 .. point_count - 1 range.

point_{index}/position (Vector2): The position of the point at index. Default: Vector2(0, 0). Note: index is a value in the 0 .. point_count - 1 range.

point_{index}/right_mode (int): The right TangentMode for the point at index. Default: 0. Note: index is a value in the 0 .. point_count - 1 range.

point_{index}/right_tangent (float): The right tangent angle (in degrees) for the point at index. Default: 0.0. Note: index is a value in the 0 .. point_count - 1 range.
